nswer.\n\nText:\n-----Entities-----\nhuman_readable_id,title,description,degree\r\n11,MANUSCRIPT,\"A *MANUSCRIPT* is a written work submitted for publication in a journal or book, which may include content generated or assisted by artificial intelligence (AI) technologies, such as AI-generated text, images, data, or other materials. Depending on the extent of AI involvement, the manuscript must include proper disclosures regarding the use of AI tools during its preparation, review, or editing stages. Some descriptions emphasize that AI-assisted or AI-generated content must be clearly identified and documented to meet the rigorous standards of scientific and scholarly assessment. Additionally, certain policies, such as those outlined by Emerald, require compliance with specific guidelines on AI usage and content creation. The manuscript must also undergo standard editorial processes, including editing and fact-checking, to ensure accuracy and integrity. Overall, the inclusion of AI-generated or AI-assisted content necessitates transparency and adherence to ethical and procedural standards in academic publishing.\",25\r\n119,AI ASSISTED COPY EDITING,\"AI Assisted Copy Editing is a process where artificial intelligence is utilized to enhance the readability and stylistic quality of human-generated texts without modifying the underlying content. This approach leverages AI technologies to support editorial tasks, focusing on improving the flow, coherence, and overall presentation of written material while preserving the original meaning and intent of the author. It represents a growing intersection between academic publishing and AI governance, as the integration of such tools raises important questions about authorship, editorial responsibility, and the role of automation in scholarly communication.\",3\r\n94,ARTISTIC RENDERINGS,\"The entity \"\"ARTISTIC RENDERINGS\"\" refers to visual content created through the use of generative AI tools, including images and other graphical elements. This category encompasses tasks that involve the application of AI in generating artistic or illustrative material, such as cover art or graphical abstracts. Such outputs may require disclosure depending on the context or institutional guidelines, highlighting the growing importance of transparency in the use of AI within academic and creative domains. The integration of AI in producing artistic renderings raises questions about authorship, originality, and ethical considerations in both academic publishing and broader artistic practices.\",2\r\n12,CONTENT,\"The entity \"\"CONTENT\"\" refers to any material submitted to a journal, including text, audio, video, and other formats, which may involve AI technology. It encompasses the information, text, or data included in a manuscript, which must be verified for originality and accuracy when generated by AI. This includes the material presented in a manuscript, such as text, images, and other forms of media, as well as the text, figures, or other material included in a manuscript, which may be generated by AI and must be disclosed. The definition emphasizes the need for transparency and verification, particularly when AI is involved in the creation of the content.\",3\r\n32,ACKNOWLEDGEMENTS,\"A section of a manuscript where authors may disclose the use of AI tools\"\"\",1\r\n142,AI SIMILARITY INDEX,\"A tool used by journals to detect AI-generated content in manuscripts\"\"\",1\r\n31,METHODS,\"A section of a manuscript where authors describe the methods used, including the use of AI tools\"\"\",1\r\n121,NATURE PORTFOLIO,\"A publisher of academic journals that sets standards for publication, including requirements for editing and fact-checking manuscripts\"\"\",1\r\n\n\n-----Relationships-----\nhuman_readable_id,source,target,description,rank\r\n101,AUTHOR,MANUSCRIPT,\"Authors are responsible for the content of their manuscripts, including any AI-generated or AI-assisted elements, and must ensure proper 