tent and methodology presented in manuscripts. Additionally, the peer review process may include checks for the use of artificial intelligence in manuscripts, with guidelines suggesting that AI should only be employed in limited and transparent ways during the research and writing phases. The integration of AI in this context remains a topic of ongoing discussion within academic and publishing communities.\",57\r\n232,MANUSCRIPT,ETHICAL USE,Manuscripts must be prepared using AI technology in an ethical manner,56\r\n229,MANUSCRIPT,DISCLOSURE,Manuscripts may require disclosure of AI usage during submission or peer review,53\r\n76,AI TECHNOLOGY,CONTENT,\"Content submitted to journals may involve the use of AI technologies, which must be disclosed\",51\r\n231,MANUSCRIPT,TRANSPARENCY,Manuscripts must be transparent about the use of AI technology,51\r\n14,GENERATIVE AI,MANUSCRIPT,\"Generative AI may be used to create or enhance content in a manuscript, which must be disclosed, and it may also be used for copy editing, though not for creating original content, which similarly requires disclosure. These guidelines apply to the use of Generative AI in relation to Manuscript development, emphasizing transparency and accountability in the integration of AI technologies within academic publishing processes.\",49\r\n224,MANUSCRIPT,AUTHORSHIP,\"The entity \"\"MANUSCRIPT\"\" refers to an academic work that must comply with established authorship guidelines, which dictate that \"\"AUTHORSHIP\"\" is determined based on contributions to the manuscript and its preparation. Additionally, manuscripts are required to include proper disclosure of AI usage, ensuring transparency in the research process. These guidelines underscore the interdependence between the manuscript and authorship, as the integrity of both is maintained through clear attribution of contributions and responsible use of artificial intelligence in scholarly output.\",48\r\n230,MANUSCRIPT,RIGHTS PROTECTION,Manuscripts m